article.headline: Wright St. 64, Ill.-Chicago 47
article.story: CHICAGO -- Vaughn Duggins scored 17 points Saturday to lead Wright State to a 64-47 victory over Illinois-Chicago. Todd Brown scored 13 points and Cory Cooperwood 10 points and seven rebounds for the Raiders (10-5, 3-1 Horizon). Wright State led 29-25 at the half, then shot 58 percent from the field in the second half and built its lead up to 25 points with under four minutes to play. The Raiders finished at 46 percent for the game. Zavion Neely led the Flames (5-9, 1-3) with 14 points. Illinois-Chicago shot 41 percent in the first half but went just 7-for-28 (25 percent) from the field after halftime to finish the game at 31 percent. Wright State finished with a 38-29 rebounding edge.
